cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper focuses on optimizing data movement in parallel data-intensive applications, which is a common problem in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes a new technique for optimizing existing libraries, which falls under the category of programming languages and compilers. Hence, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the second likely category. The paper also discusses correctness constraints and parallelization, which are related to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely category as well. The paper also presents performance gains, which can be considered as a machine learning problem, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with data-intensive applications, which can be related to databases, making cs.DB (Databases) a possible category.
